1. Settings -> Trackpad -> Tap to click
2. Clean the dock
3. Delete all unnecessary App from the Applications
4. Finder -> Settings; from the top of the Menu-bar
5. Command + Shift + . -> To show/hide the hidden gems ðŸ˜‚

6. Create a Developer folder to see the Apple's Magic
7. Turn off notifications
8. brew install : /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
9. Don't forget to the Next Step at the Terminal, Just copy -> paste -> return/Enter
10. Customize the .zshrc from Terminal: 
      a. nano ~/.zshrc
      b. PROMPT='%n:~$'  or PROMPT='customusername~$'  or https://www.makeuseof.com/customize-zsh-prompt-macos-terminal/  furthur exploration
11. Install java,node,python3
12. Install Miniconda or Anaconda; use brew
13. Quit the Terminal and relaunch it and enter "conda env list"
14. Run 'conda init' before 'conda deactivate'  TODAY IS 14th FEB 2025

15. Install Docker
16. Configure SSH and GPG keys for the GitHub  : https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent
    a. ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"  or  ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com"
    b. pbcopy < ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub

